    m_Localized: Independence Day is on 11 November.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 80874528316579860
    m_Localized: We play football at the National Stadium.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 80874528316579861
    m_Localized: The Polish flag is white and red.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 80874528316579862
    m_Localized: You can find her on the city coat of arms and all over Warsaw.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 80874528316579863
    m_Localized: She is half woman, half fish, and carries a sword and a shield.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 80874528316579864
    m_Localized: You can find her on the city coat of arms and all over Warsaw.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 80874528316579865
    m_Localized: Every summer, free piano concerts are held here on Sundays.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 80874528316579866
    m_Localized: "This monument stands in \u0141azienki Park in Warsaw."
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 80874528316579867
    m_Localized: Every summer, free piano concerts are held here on Sundays.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 80874528316579868
    m_Localized: Fryderyk Chopin was born near Warsaw in 1810.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 80874528316579869
    m_Localized: Their names are said to be hidden inside the name "Warszawa."
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 80874528316579870
    m_Localized: Wars and Sawa are characters from an old legend about Warsaw.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 80874528316579871
    m_Localized: Their names are said to be hidden inside the name "Warszawa."
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 80874528316579872
    m_Localized: His column on Castle Square is one of the oldest secular monuments
      in Warsaw.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 80874528316579873
    m_Localized: "King Sigismund III Vasa moved the capital of Poland from Krak\xF3w
      to Warsaw in 1596."
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 80874528316579874
    m_Localized: His column on Castle Square is one of the oldest secular monuments
      in Warsaw.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 80874528316579875
    m_Localized: The Royal Castle stands right next to the column.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 80874528316579876
    m_Localized: It meets in Warsaw and votes on the laws of Poland.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 80874528316579877
    m_Localized: The Polish parliament is called the Sejm and the Senate.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 80874528316579878
    m_Localized: It meets in Warsaw and votes on the laws of Poland.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 80874528316579879
    m_Localized: "The Presidential Palace is nearby on Krakowskie Przedmie\u015Bcie."
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 80874528316579880
    m_Localized: The Palace of Culture and Science is the tallest building in Poland.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 80874528316579881
    m_Localized: It was built in the 1950s and has a viewing terrace at the top.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 80874528316579882
    m_Localized: "Maria Sk\u0142odowska-Curie was born in Warsaw in 1867."
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 80874528316579883
    m_Localized: She was the first woman to win a Nobel Prize, and she won it twice.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 80874528316579884
    m_Localized: "The PGE Narodowy stands on the right bank of the Wis\u0142a."
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 80874528316579885
    m_Localized: It opened in 2012 and hosted matches during UEFA Euro 2012.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 80874528316579886
    m_Localized: Robert Lewandowski is one of Poland's most famous footballers.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 80874528316579887
    m_Localized: He has scored hundreds of goals for club and country.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 83574578339635200
    m_Localized: Draw your favorite place in Warsaw!
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 83574578343829504
    m_Localized: Warsaw's story starts with the Mermaid, not with me.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 83574578343829505
    m_Localized: Talk to the people in each place to keep going.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 83574578343829506
    m_Localized: You already helped me, thank you! The chest is waiting for you here.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 83574578343829507
    m_Localized: I am the Mermaid of Warsaw. I am a symbol of the city.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 83574578343829508
    m_Localized: Let us sort the ways people move around Warsaw!
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 83574578343829509
    m_Localized: I saw Antura run past Copernicus and toward the river with the Mermaid's
      sword.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 83574578343829510
    m_Localized: The Chopin chest is open now.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 83574578343829511
    m_Localized: Go north-east and help Wars and Sawa by the Wisla.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 83574578343829512
    m_Localized: Chopin needs help first. Then come to the river.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 83574578343829513
    m_Localized: Sawa is waiting by the river bend. Speak with her, then come back
      to Wars.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 83574578343829514
    m_Localized: Sawa is back! Talk to us both to hear the rest of our story.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 83574578343829515
    m_Localized: "I am Sawa. The Wis\u0142a is the longest river in Poland and this
      is our home."
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 83574578343829516
    m_Localized: We are together again. Thank you.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 83574578343829517
    m_Localized: Our story is one of the old stories of Warsaw.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 83574578343829518
    m_Localized: The Wisla flows through Warsaw, and our story is part of the city.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 83574578343829519
    m_Localized: Antura passed toward King Sigismund's Column in the old town.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 83574578343829520
    m_Localized: Our chest is open now.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 83574578343829521
    m_Localized: Go west to the old town square and speak with King Sigismund. He
      may know where the sword was left.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 83574578343829522
    m_Localized: Help Wars and Sawa first, then come to my square.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 83574578343829523
    m_Localized: My crown is restored. The chest is yours.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 83574578343829524
    m_Localized: I am King Sigismund. My column stands in the old town near the Royal
      Castle.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 83574578343829525
    m_Localized: People remember me because the capital moved to Warsaw.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 83574578343829526
    m_Localized: I heard the Mermaid's sword was left at the Houses of Parliament.
