  - m_Id: 86121538217042001
    m_Localized: Wars and Sawa are characters from an old legend about Warsaw.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 86121538217042002
    m_Localized: Their names are said to be hidden inside the name "Warszawa."
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 86121538217042003
    m_Localized: "King Sigismund III Vasa moved the capital of Poland from Krak\xF3w
      to Warsaw in 1596."
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 86121538217042004
    m_Localized: "King Sigismund III Vasa moved the capital of Poland from Krak\xF3w
      to Warsaw in 1596."
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 86121538217042005
    m_Localized: His column on Castle Square is one of the oldest secular monuments
      in Warsaw.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 86121538217042006
    m_Localized: The Royal Castle stands right next to the column.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 86121538217042007
    m_Localized: The Polish parliament is called the Sejm and the Senate.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 86121538217042008
    m_Localized: The Polish parliament is called the Sejm and the Senate.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 86121538217042009
    m_Localized: It meets in Warsaw and votes on the laws of Poland.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 86121538217042010
    m_Localized: "The Presidential Palace is nearby on Krakowskie Przedmie\u015Bcie."
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 86121538217042011
    m_Localized: The Palace of Culture and Science is the tallest building in Poland.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 86121538217042012
    m_Localized: It was built in the 1950s and has a viewing terrace at the top.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 86121538217042013
    m_Localized: "Maria Sk\u0142odowska-Curie was born in Warsaw in 1867."
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 86121538217042014
    m_Localized: "The PGE Narodowy stands on the right bank of the Wis\u0142a."
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 86121538217042015
    m_Localized: It opened in 2012 and hosted matches during UEFA Euro 2012.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 86121538217042016
    m_Localized: Robert Lewandowski is one of Poland's most famous footballers.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 86180920980135936
    m_Localized: You found all keys! Now go and unlock the chest!
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 86180920984330240
    m_Localized: "Now go to the Wars and Sawa statue by the Wis\u0142a river."
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 86180920984330241
    m_Localized: Now let us see what you remember about this adventure
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 86180920984330242
    m_Localized: Good try. You can explore the city again and learn more.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 86180920984330243
    m_Localized: Bikes are a simple way to move from place to place.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 86180920984330244
    m_Localized: Sawa is waiting by the river bend. Speak with her, then come back
      to Wars.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 86180920984330245
    m_Localized: "Please find her at the bend of the Wis\u0142a and bring her back
      to me."
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 86180920984330246
    m_Localized: Our story is one of the old stories of Warsaw.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 86180920984330247
    m_Localized: Antura passed toward King Sigismund's Column in the old town.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
